<subSubSection box="[199,810,909,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,800,1979]" box="[199,810,909,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,909,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the 
<typeStatus box="[450,498,909,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">type</typeStatus>
locality, Patagonian Andes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="576" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,800,1979]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,320,944,971]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Silva &amp; Pinho, 2020" authorityName="Silva &amp; Pinho" authorityYear="2020" box="[462,680,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patagonica" status="sp. n." subGenus="Macropelopia">
<emphasis box="[462,493,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[508,539,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[554,680,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[686,748,945,971]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[686,748,945,971]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from those of other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thienemann in Thienemann &amp; Kieffer" authorityYear="1916" box="[1045,1200,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1045,1200,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Macropelopia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in the combination of the following characters: temporals bi- to triserial; tibial comb of four long bristles present on foreleg; wing translucid, but darkened only around Cu, MCu, RM and bases of R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[925,933,1034,1048]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">1</subScript>
, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[968,993,1034,1048]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1067,1093,1034,1048]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">4+5</subScript>
; hypopygium with gonostylus broad basally and constricted in apical 1/3; and gonocoxite lacking inferior volsella.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="578" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,800,1979]" box="[199,345,1088,1115]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1088,1115]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Description.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,800,1979]" box="[199,412,1125,1151]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis box="[199,321,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Adult male</emphasis>
(n = 2).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,800,1979]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis box="[199,244,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Size</emphasis>
. Total length 4.0– 
<quantity box="[453,542,1161,1187]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" unit="mm" value="4.3">4.3 mm</quantity>
. Wing length 
<quantity box="[701,840,1161,1187]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.4">2.4–2.6 mm</quantity>
. Total length / wing length 1.66–1.67. Wing length / length of profemur 2.57–2.59.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,800,1979]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis box="[199,322,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Coloration</emphasis>
. Head brown; thorax dark brown, except for pale anterior anepisternum II and halter; abdomen dark brown with narrow paler stripe between segments. Legs light brown with dark brown base of tibia and apices of femur and tibia. Wing translucid, darkened only around Cu, MCu, RM and bases of R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1112,1120,1322,1336]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">1</subScript>
, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1153,1178,1322,1336]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1249,1275,1322,1336]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">4+5</subScript>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,800,1979]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[275,365,1341,1367]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,541,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,541,1946]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Macropelopia (Macropelopia) patagonica sp. n., adult male. (A) Head, frontal view. (B) Thorax. (C) Wing. (D–F) Tibial spurs of P 1 (D), P 2 (E) and P 3 (F). (G) Hypopygium with tergite IX, dorsal view (left) and ventral view (right)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3661892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3661892/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Antenna lost. Eye bridge nearly parallel-sided with 5–6 ommatidia width. Temporal setae 28– 30, bi to triserial. Clypeus 103–108 μm long, 108–113 μm wide at broadest point, bearing 16–18 setae. Tentorium 162–179 μm long, 34–49 μm wide; stipes 157–162 μm long. First to fifth palpomere lengths (μm): 49–54, 64–69, 118–132, 157–181, 245–265.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,800,1979]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[296,383,1485,1511]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,541,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,541,1946]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Macropelopia (Macropelopia) patagonica sp. n., adult male. (A) Head, frontal view. (B) Thorax. (C) Wing. (D–F) Tibial spurs of P 1 (D), P 2 (E) and P 3 (F). (G) Hypopygium with tergite IX, dorsal view (left) and ventral view (right)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3661892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3661892/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Scutal tubercle distinct. Antepronotum with 10–11 setae. Dorsocentrals 39–45, uni- to triserial; acrostichals 51–58; prealars 16–19; supraalar 1; preespisternals 3; anepisternals absent; postnotals 5–6. Scutellum with 32–36 setae multiserially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,800,1979]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis box="[199,257,1594,1619]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[273,362,1593,1619]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,541,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,541,1946]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Macropelopia (Macropelopia) patagonica sp. n., adult male. (A) Head, frontal view. (B) Thorax. (C) Wing. (D–F) Tibial spurs of P 1 (D), P 2 (E) and P 3 (F). (G) Hypopygium with tergite IX, dorsal view (left) and ventral view (right)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3661892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3661892/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Width 
<quantity box="[461,627,1593,1619]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.55" metricValueMax="7.9" metricValueMin="7.199999999999999" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" unit="mm" value="0.755" valueMax="0.79" valueMin="0.72">0.72–0.79 mm</quantity>
, membrane completely covered with macrotrichia. VR 0.94–0.95. WW 0.30. Costal vein produced beyond R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[571,597,1646,1660]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">4+5</subScript>
, its protrusion 118–128 μm long. R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1000,1008,1646,1660]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">2</subScript>
present; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1131,1156,1646,1660]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">2+3</subScript>
distinct, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1280,1288,1646,1660]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">3</subScript>
not reaching costa. MCu just beyond FCu. Anal lobe weakly developed. Brachiolum with 4–5 setae; Rs, M and Cu with setae. Squama with 24–26 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,800,1979]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis box="[199,252,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[267,333,1737,1763]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,541,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,541,1946]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Macropelopia (Macropelopia) patagonica sp. n., adult male. (A) Head, frontal view. (B) Thorax. (C) Wing. (D–F) Tibial spurs of P 1 (D), P 2 (E) and P 3 (F). (G) Hypopygium with tergite IX, dorsal view (left) and ventral view (right)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3661892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3661892/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Figs 1</figureCitation>
D–F). Fore leg: apex of tibia 59–64 μm wide, with single spur 59 (1) μm long, bearing 8–9 lateral teeth (
<figureCitation box="[221,310,1773,1799]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,541,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,541,1946]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Macropelopia (Macropelopia) patagonica sp. n., adult male. (A) Head, frontal view. (B) Thorax. (C) Wing. (D–F) Tibial spurs of P 1 (D), P 2 (E) and P 3 (F). (G) Hypopygium with tergite IX, dorsal view (left) and ventral view (right)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3661892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3661892/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
); comb with 5–6 strong bristles, longest 
<quantity box="[769,913,1773,1799]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.185" metricValueMax="1.29" metricValueMin="1.08" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" unit="mm" value="118.5" valueMax="129.0" valueMin="108.0">108–129 µm</quantity>
long; ta 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1005,1030,1790,1804]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">1–4</subScript>
without preapical pseudospurs. Mid leg: apex of tibia 59–64 μm wide, with two spurs 59–64 and 44–49 μm long, each bearing 8–11 lateral teeth (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,541,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,541,1946]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Macropelopia (Macropelopia) patagonica sp. n., adult male. (A) Head, frontal view. (B) Thorax. (C) Wing. (D–F) Tibial spurs of P 1 (D), P 2 (E) and P 3 (F). (G) Hypopygium with tergite IX, dorsal view (left) and ventral view (right)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3661892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3661892/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
); ta 
<subScript attach="left" box="[227,252,1862,1876]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">1–4</subScript>
without preapical pseudospurs. Hind leg: apex of tibia 64–69 μm wide, with two spurs 69–74 and 49–54 μm long, each bearing 8–11 lateral teeth (
<figureCitation box="[630,716,1881,1907]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,541,1941]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[164,1423,541,1946]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Macropelopia (Macropelopia) patagonica sp. n., adult male. (A) Head, frontal view. (B) Thorax. (C) Wing. (D–F) Tibial spurs of P 1 (D), P 2 (E) and P 3 (F). (G) Hypopygium with tergite IX, dorsal view (left) and ventral view (right)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3661892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3661892/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
); comb with 5–12 strong bristles, longest 
<quantity box="[1199,1316,1880,1907]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.15" metricValueMax="5.4" metricValueMin="4.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" unit="mm" value="51.5" valueMax="54.0" valueMin="49.0">49–54 µm</quantity>
long; ta 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1412,1436,1898,1912]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">1–4</subScript>
without preapical pseudospurs. Claws on all legs long, slender, distally pointed and spinulate in basal ⅓. Pulvilli very small. Lengths (μm) and proportions of legs as in 
