<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="578" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,333,359]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Remarks</emphasis>
. The male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Silva &amp; Pinho, 2020" authorityName="Silva &amp; Pinho" authorityYear="2020" box="[476,956,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patagonica" status="sp. n." subGenus="Macropelopia">
<emphasis box="[476,634,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Macropelopia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[653,811,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Macropelopia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[830,956,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[966,1033,333,359]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[966,1033,333,359]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
possesses a tibial comb consisting of long bristles on the foreleg, which is unique among the species of this genus. Partial COI gene sequences were obtained from 
<specimenCount box="[318,471,405,431]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" type="generic">18 specimens</specimenCount>
of 5 species belonging to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thienemann in Thienemann &amp; Kieffer" authorityYear="1916" box="[887,1045,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[887,1045,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Macropelopia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1060,1160,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1939,1964]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,805,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,805,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Neighbor joining tree for species of the genus Macropelopia based on partial COI sequences (DNA barcodes) and the Kimura-2-parameter. Numbers on branches are bootstrap values." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3661894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3661894/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Figure 2</figureCitation>
). The aligned sequences were partially (88.9 %) 658 base pairs long with 161 variable sites (24.5%), of which 86 (47.5%) were potentially parsimony informative. The specimens identified morphologically as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thienemann in Thienemann &amp; Kieffer" authorityYear="1916" box="[936,1094,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[936,1094,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Macropelopia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were divided into at least five separate barcode species (
<figureCitation box="[443,542,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1939,1964]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,805,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,805,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Neighbor joining tree for species of the genus Macropelopia based on partial COI sequences (DNA barcodes) and the Kimura-2-parameter. Numbers on branches are bootstrap values." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3661894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3661894/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Figure 2</figureCitation>
). However, we did not observe all the material in order to differentiate the species in these clusters into subgenera. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thienemann in Thienemann &amp; Kieffer" authorityYear="1916" box="[723,881,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[723,881,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Macropelopia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[1084,1198,549,575]" name="Argentina" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1209,1288,549,575]" name="France" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">France</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1299,1389,549,575]" name="Norway" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Norway</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,340,585,611]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">United Kingdom</collectingCountry>
(
<tableCitation box="[353,437,585,611]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,239,658,682]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="TABLE 1. List of analysed specimens with associated sample localities, voucher reference numbers and GenBank accessions. The dash (-) indicates that no information is available." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/C6F866195C13FFBE1F99FD6EFCB674C0" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" tableUuid="C6F866195C13FFBE1F99FD6EFCB674C0">Table 1</tableCitation>
). The analysis of partial DNA barcode sequences supports 
<taxonomicName authority="Silva &amp; Pinho, 2020" authorityName="Silva &amp; Pinho" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patagonica" status="sp. n." subGenus="Macropelopia">
<emphasis box="[1096,1254,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Macropelopia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1269,1427,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Macropelopia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[151,277,622,647]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[285,350,621,647]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[285,350,621,647]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
as valid species. Moreover, we found COI suitable for summarizing the sequence diversity and detecting taxonomically challenging species within the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thienemann in Thienemann &amp; Kieffer" authorityYear="1916" box="[846,1004,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[846,1004,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Macropelopia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="578" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,755]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,693,719]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Ecology</emphasis>
. Adult males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Silva &amp; Pinho, 2020" authorityName="Silva &amp; Pinho" authorityYear="2020" box="[475,946,693,719]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Macropelopia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patagonica" status="sp. n." subGenus="Macropelopia">
<emphasis box="[475,633,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Macropelopia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[647,805,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Macropelopia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[820,946,694,719]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[951,1014,693,719]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[951,1014,693,719]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
were collected at a high altitude in the margins of a glacial lake, located at Parque Nacional Nahuel Huapi, on the Patagonian Andes.
</paragraph>
